OL,6,FMr Findlay called for a non-custodial
OL,7,Fsentence and said: "Prison may be
OL,8,Fpunitive and cause Mr Loy more harm
OL,9,Fthan good.
OL,11,F"Imprisoning Jake Loy won't make him a
OL,12,Fbetter person, it won't bring anybody
OL,13,Fback."
OL,15,FThe court heard the other driver had
OL,16,Fbeen adhering to the 60mph speed limit
OL,17,Fand although Loy's speed was
OL,18,F"unknown", it would have exceeded this.
